│ P->replaceAllUsesWith(isa<Constant>(E) ? E : &*VMap.lookup(E));                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                        │
│ The problem occurs when `VMap.lookup(E)` returns a null pointer, and the code attempts to dereference  │
│ it. To fix this, we need to add a check to ensure that `VMap.lookup(E)` is valid before dereferencing  │
│ it. If it is null, we should handle the case gracefully.                                               │
│                                                                                                        │
│ ### Proposed Fix:                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                        │
│ Replace the problematic line with the following:                                                       │
│                                                                                                        │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                 │
│ if (Value *MappedValue = VMap.lookup(E)) {                                                             │
│   P->replaceAllUsesWith(isa<Constant>(E) ? E : &*MappedValue);                                         │
│ } else {                                                                                               │
│   llvm_unreachable("Expected value not found in VMap");                                                │
│ }                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                        │
│ This ensures that we only dereference `VMap.lookup(E)` if it is valid. If it is null, we trigger an    │
│ error with `llvm_unreachable`, which is a safer way to handle unexpected conditions.                   │
│                                                                                                        │
